Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook and stir 4 minutes or until cooked through. Add vegetables, pineapple with juice and sweet and sour sauce; mix well. Stir in water. Bring to boil. Stir in rice; cover. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes or until almost all of the liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.